{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["# 00 - Environment Setup and Dataset Overview\n","\n","This notebook is the entry point for the regression resource pack. It verifies the environment, loads both datasets, inspects schema/quality, and creates the first visual understanding before modelling."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Learning objectives\n","\n","By the end of this notebook, students should be able to:\n","\n","1. Confirm that all required libraries are installed.\n","2. Load CSV files safely using relative paths.\n","3. Inspect rows, columns, data types, missing values, and summary statistics.\n","4. Visualize target distributions and important numeric relationships.\n","5. Understand which dataset belongs to each regression notebook."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 1. Import libraries\n","\n","We use `pandas` and `numpy` for data handling, `matplotlib` for visualization, and `importlib.metadata` to verify installed package versions."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["from pathlib import Path\n","from importlib.metadata import version, PackageNotFoundError\n","\n","import numpy as np\n","import pandas as pd\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","pd.set_option('display.max_columns', 50)\n","pd.set_option('display.width', 120)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 2. Check package versions\n","\n","This makes the notebook reproducible. If a student's output differs, the first thing to check is the installed library version."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["packages = ['numpy', 'pandas', 'scikit-learn', 'statsmodels', 'matplotlib']\n","\n","for pkg in packages:\n","    try:\n","        print(f'{pkg:15s}: {version(pkg)}')\n","    except PackageNotFoundError:\n","        print(f'{pkg:15s}: NOT INSTALLED')"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 3. Resolve dataset paths\n","\n","The code works whether you open the notebook from the repository root or from the `notebooks/` folder."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["CWD = Path.cwd()\n","DATA_DIR = CWD.parent / 'data' if (CWD.parent / 'data').exists() else CWD / 'data'\n","\n","simple_path = DATA_DIR / 'simple_linear_student_scores.csv'\n","multiple_path = DATA_DIR / 'multiple_regression_marketing_sales.csv'\n","\n","print('Current directory:', CWD)\n","print('Data directory   :', DATA_DIR.resolve())\n","print('Simple CSV exists:', simple_path.exists())\n","print('Multiple CSV exists:', multiple_path.exists())"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 4. Load datasets\n","\n","The first dataset is for **simple linear regression**. The second dataset is for **multiple linear regression** and diagnostics."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["student_scores = pd.read_csv(simple_path)\n","marketing_sales = pd.read_csv(multiple_path)\n","\n","overview = pd.DataFrame({\n","    'dataset': ['simple_linear_student_scores.csv', 'multiple_regression_marketing_sales.csv'],\n","    'rows': [len(student_scores), len(marketing_sales)],\n","    'columns': [student_scores.shape[1], marketing_sales.shape[1]],\n","    'target': ['exam_score', 'sales_k_units'],\n","    'notebook': ['01_simple_linear_regression_end_to_end.ipynb', '02_multiple_linear_regression_end_to_end.ipynb']\n","})\n","overview"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 5. Preview the simple regression dataset\n","\n","The modelling question is: **Can we predict exam score from study hours?**"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["student_scores.head(10)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 6. Preview the multiple regression dataset\n","\n","The modelling question is: **Can we predict sales from marketing spend, price, competitor spend, and season?**"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["marketing_sales.head(10)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 7. Schema and missing-value audit\n","\n","Before modelling, always validate data types and missing values. Regression will fail or mislead if the schema is wrong."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["def audit_frame(df: pd.DataFrame, name: str) -> pd.DataFrame:\n","    return pd.DataFrame({\n","        'dataset': name,\n","        'column': df.columns,\n","        'dtype': [str(dtype) for dtype in df.dtypes],\n","        'missing_count': df.isna().sum().values,\n","        'missing_pct': (df.isna().mean().values * 100).round(2),\n","        'n_unique': df.nunique().values\n","    })\n","\n","pd.concat([\n","    audit_frame(student_scores, 'student_scores'),\n","    audit_frame(marketing_sales, 'marketing_sales')\n",""])"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 8. Summary statistics\n","\n","Summary statistics help detect unrealistic ranges, outliers, and basic scale differences."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["student_scores.describe().round(2)"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["marketing_sales.describe().round(2)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 9. Visualize target distributions\n","\n","The target distribution affects model interpretation. A heavily skewed target may require transformation or robust modelling."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))\n","\n","axes[0].hist(student_scores['exam_score'], bins=12, edgecolor='black')\n","axes[0].set_title('Distribution of exam_score')\n","axes[0].set_xlabel('Exam score')\n","axes[0].set_ylabel('Count')\n","\n","axes[1].hist(marketing_sales['sales_k_units'], bins=14, edgecolor='black')\n","axes[1].set_title('Distribution of sales_k_units')\n","axes[1].set_xlabel('Sales, thousand units')\n","axes[1].set_ylabel('Count')\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 10. Visualize key relationships\n","\n","Regression begins with relationship inspection. We want to know whether the relationship is roughly linear before fitting a linear model."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))\n","plt.scatter(student_scores['study_hours'], student_scores['exam_score'], alpha=0.8)\n","plt.title('Study hours vs exam score')\n","plt.xlabel('Study hours')\n","plt.ylabel('Exam score')\n","plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n","plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["numeric_cols = ['tv_spend_k', 'radio_spend_k', 'social_spend_k', 'price_index', 'competitor_spend_k', 'sales_k_units']\n","corr = marketing_sales[numeric_cols].corr()\n","\n","fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))\n","im = ax.imshow(corr, vmin=-1, vmax=1)\n","ax.set_xticks(range(len(corr.columns)))\n","ax.set_yticks(range(len(corr.columns)))\n","ax.set_xticklabels(corr.columns, rotation=45, ha='right')\n","ax.set_yticklabels(corr.columns)\n","ax.set_title('Correlation heatmap for marketing dataset')\n","fig.colorbar(im, ax=ax, fraction=0.046, pad=0.04)\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 11. Notebook map\n","\n","| Notebook | Main focus |\n","|---|---|\n","| `01_simple_linear_regression_end_to_end.ipynb` | Simple regression, OLS formula, fitted line, residuals |\n","| `02_multiple_linear_regression_end_to_end.ipynb` | Multiple regression, categorical encoding, sklearn pipeline, statsmodels |\n","| `03_diagnostics_regularization_and_interpretability.ipynb` | Assumptions, VIF, Ridge, Lasso, model comparison |\n","\n","Move to notebook 01 after completing this overview."]}],"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.13.5","mimetype":"text/x-python","file_extension":".py","pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":5}